16 KB Verification
------------------

After the build, verify at least the arm64 libraries.

Example:

```sh
"$ANDROID_NDK_ROOT/toolchains/llvm/prebuilt/darwin-x86_64/bin/llvm-readelf" -l \
  android/libs/arm64-v8a/libffmpegkit.so

"$ANDROID_NDK_ROOT/toolchains/llvm/prebuilt/darwin-x86_64/bin/llvm-readelf" -l \
  android/libs/arm64-v8a/libc++_shared.so
```

Expected result:

- all `LOAD` segments should show `Align 0x4000`

It is also reasonable to verify the AAR itself:

```sh
unzip -p android/ffmpeg-kit-android-lib/build/outputs/aar/ffmpeg-kit-release.aar \
  jni/arm64-v8a/libffmpegkit.so > /tmp/libffmpegkit.so

"$ANDROID_NDK_ROOT/toolchains/llvm/prebuilt/darwin-x86_64/bin/llvm-readelf" -l \
  /tmp/libffmpegkit.so
```

Notes
-----

- `src/*` contains downloaded/upstream nested repositories used by the build.
  They are not part of the top-level repo history.
- The build generates outputs under `.tmp/`, `prebuilt/`, `android/libs/`,
  `android/obj/`, and `android/ffmpeg-kit-android-lib/build/`.
- Some IDEs may still show generated files or nested repos under `src/*`.
- `tools/android/.gradle/` is local IDE/Gradle cache noise.
- If switching machines or build paths, forcing rebuild of the enabled
  dependencies is safer than trying to reuse old `prebuilt/*` metadata.
